description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS SECONDMENT FOR 6 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a band 5 nurse to join the busy forward thinking Urology department at Cwm Taf Morgannwg University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of caring for urological patients is desirable, but not essential as training will be provided, encouraged and supported for the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that the successful candidate is a team player who has excellent communication skills, and has the desire to continuously learn and be motivated to progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will be a 6 month secondment to cover maternity leave. It will be based at the Royal Glamorgan Hospital, however, the successful candidate will be required to work across all sites as and when required in accordance with the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in this role?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keryn Jones – Lead Urology Nurse on 01685721721 ext 23014.&lt;/p&gt;
